Thank you. Good night.

225
00:18:24.395 --> 00:18:27.954 line:82%
I don't love Anjali. She's my friend!

226
00:18:28.905 --> 00:18:30.109 line:82%
She's my friend.

227
00:18:30.193 --> 00:18:31.311 line:82%
No one wants to listen.

228
00:18:31.964 --> 00:18:33.850 line:82%
I don't care if you don't want
to listen to me.

229
00:18:35.198 --> 00:18:38.740 line:82%
She's my friend!

230
00:19:03.089 --> 00:19:04.182 line:82%
You were right.

231
00:19:07.376 --> 00:19:08.407 line:82%
I love Anjali.

232
00:19:20.451 --> 00:19:21.693 line:82%
Men are dogs.

233
00:19:23.572 --> 00:19:24.956 line:82%
We're very selfish.

234
00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:30.497 line:82%
If you insist, I'll agree.

235
00:19:32.568 --> 00:19:33.635 line:82%
No, it's true.

236
00:19:35.008 --> 00:19:36.129 line:82%
Men are dogs.

237
00:19:38.136 --> 00:19:39.846 line:82%
We take things for granted so easily.

238
00:19:42.390 --> 00:19:44.854 line:82%
And our convictions are so convenient.

239
00:19:47.266 --> 00:19:50.773 line:82%
I concluded so conveniently
that Anjali was mine.

240
00:19:52.734 --> 00:19:58.242 line:82%
I mean, she'd always be
where she was,

241
00:20:00.575 --> 00:20:05.552 line:82%
waiting for me to marry her
when it was convenient for me.

242
00:20:09.417 --> 00:20:12.767 line:82%
I never considered that she was human.

243
00:20:14.562 --> 00:20:16.382 line:82%
That she had her own desires and dreams.

244
00:20:19.427 --> 00:20:23.007 line:82%
But what if I'm not part of her dreams?

245
00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:30.186 line:82%
I never thought someone else
would come into her life.

246
00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:39.465 line:82%
But how could Anjali know something
I never admitted to myself?

247
00:20:43.785 --> 00:20:45.137 line:82%
But how could I have told her?

248
00:20:47.914 --> 00:20:50.683 line:82%
I've only just now realizes
how dearly I love her.

249
00:20:53.503 --> 00:20:54.754 line:82%
Today...

250
00:20:57.799 --> 00:20:59.861 line:82%
when she's about to marry someone else.

251
00:21:02.136 --> 00:21:04.112 line:82%
I understand, Sanjay.

252
00:21:05.056 --> 00:21:08.406 line:82%
Sometimes you only know what you had
when it's gone.

253
00:21:09.811 --> 00:21:12.969 line:82%
What will you do now?

254
00:21:16.687 --> 00:21:17.735 line:82%
Take the 8:40 flight.

255
00:21:21.447 --> 00:21:25.243 line:82%
You're going... to Dehradoon?

256
00:21:26.911 --> 00:21:28.006 line:82%
Yeah.

257
00:21:30.707 --> 00:21:31.909 line:82%
Sanjay...

258
00:21:33.309 --> 00:21:37.547 line:82%
I know it'll be hard for you
to see this wedding happen.

259
00:21:39.569 --> 00:21:43.761 line:82%
Anjali is about to marry
someone else and you're...

260
00:21:47.223 --> 00:21:48.307 line:82%
I'm so proud of you.

261
00:21:50.733 --> 00:21:54.022 line:82%
Ria, you don't understand.
Yes, I'm going,

262
00:21:54.897 --> 00:21:59.118 line:82%
but not to attend the wedding,
I'm going lo break it up.

263
00:21:59.986 --> 00:22:01.824 line:82%
-What?
-Yeah.

264
00:22:02.673 --> 00:22:06.701 line:82%
Anjali is about to get married,
she hasn't done it yet.

265
00:22:09.370 --> 00:22:11.494 line:82%
I'm the one she's gonna marry.

266
00:22:13.583 --> 00:22:15.735 line:82%
Because, if you follow your heart...

267
00:22:16.127 --> 00:22:17.672 line:82%
You can change the world.

268
00:22:18.206 --> 00:22:22.925 line:82%
-Exactly.
-You were right. Men are dogs.

269
00:22:47.408 --> 00:22:51.412 line:82%
♪ May joys abound ♪

270
00:22:52.121 --> 00:22:56.959 line:82%
♪ May health abound ♪

271
00:22:57.919 --> 00:23:02.298 line:82%
♪ May goodwill abound ♪

272
00:23:03.174 --> 00:23:09.055 line:82%
♪ May sorrow be dispelled ♪

273
00:23:10.848 --> 00:23:17.587 line:82%
♪ May peace abound ♪

274
00:23:23.319 --> 00:23:25.513 line:82%
Peace? How am I to keep my peace?

275
00:23:26.619 --> 00:23:31.410 line:82%
Please, don't be angry.
Anjali is like a daughter to you.

276
00:23:31.494 --> 00:23:37.278 line:82%
That's why, Vishnu.
I will hold this against you forever.

277
00:23:37.385 --> 00:23:42.088 line:82%
I'm her uncle, and you finalized
her wedding without consulting me?

278
00:23:42.171 --> 00:23:43.502 line:82%
My goodness.

279
00:23:43.586 --> 00:23:46.330 line:82%
You're making a mountain
out of a molehill.

280
00:23:46.434 --> 00:23:50.638 line:82%
You think I'm overreacting?
You judge, who's the older brother?

281
00:23:50.721 --> 00:23:53.443 line:82%
-You are my older brother.
-And I'm older than you are.

282
00:23:54.146 --> 00:23:56.102 line:82%
-I approved this match.
-Look, Mother.

283
00:23:56.185 --> 00:23:59.877 line:82%
-What's your problem?
-You're always butting in.

284
00:23:59.981 --> 00:24:02.223 line:82%
Shut up and touch the sacred fires.

285
00:24:02.316 --> 00:24:04.170 line:82%
Then give your brother a hug.

286
00:24:04.986 --> 00:24:07.860 line:82%
-Come on, brother.
-You'll get a beating someday.

287
00:24:08.698 --> 00:24:11.450 line:82%
Mother, I knew my husband
was a little afraid of you

288
00:24:11.534 --> 00:24:14.754 line:82%
but my brother-in-law too?

289
00:24:15.288 --> 00:24:18.512 line:82%
No, his wife scares him more.

290
00:24:18.833 --> 00:24:23.566 line:82%
I'm not afraid of anyone.
Pull down the wall, I say.

291
00:24:24.130 --> 00:24:27.887 line:82%
Ma, if the door isn't facing east...

292
00:24:27.967 --> 00:24:32.887 line:82%
Mother-in-law, you want to pull down walls
just for the wedding?

293
00:24:33.496 --> 00:24:36.100 line:82%
My dear anglicized son-in-law,

294
00:24:36.184 --> 00:24:39.597 line:82%
I'd rather tear down walls
than defy the scriptures.

295
00:24:39.700 --> 00:24:43.357 line:82%
Grooms never enter from the west.
Good God, it's sacrilege.

296
00:24:43.441 --> 00:24:48.057 line:82%
So what, Kappo? Lord Rama entered
from the west when he was wed.

297
00:24:48.631 --> 00:24:51.824 line:82%
-How's that?
-Ayodhya is west of Mithila.

298
00:24:51.908 --> 00:24:53.016 line:82%
How could you forget?

299
00:24:53.709 --> 00:24:59.081 line:82%
How could you forget, dear brother,
that Lord Rama was exiled for 14 years.

300
00:24:59.165 --> 00:25:03.082 line:82%
Had he observed the scriptures
Lord Rama would've been fine.

301
00:25:03.639 --> 00:25:05.628 line:82%
Can you match that?

302
00:25:05.711 --> 00:25:09.175 line:82%
Our sister-in-law is matchless.

303
00:25:10.343 --> 00:25:12.426 line:82%
I've finally convinced him.

304
00:25:12.511 --> 00:25:17.837 line:82%
I wonder if I could've
convinced him to get married.

305
00:25:20.599 --> 00:25:23.189 line:82%
Anju's wedding is going to be fun.

306
00:25:23.882 --> 00:25:26.422 line:82%
My sister-in-law happens to be
everyone's favorite.

307
00:25:26.525 --> 00:25:28.945 line:82%
And our wedding was not less grand.

308
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:33.960 line:82%
Yes, but there's no sign of that guy
who entertained everyone at your wedding.

309
00:25:34.033 --> 00:25:36.098 line:82%
-Who?
-Sanju.

310
00:25:36.162 --> 00:25:37.218 line:82%
Yes!

311
00:25:47.338 --> 00:25:50.683 line:82%
You escaped from the Aunt, fatso.
I'll pull your hair and make you short.

312
00:25:54.929 --> 00:25:56.821 line:82%
-Bahadur Singh!
-Yes, ma'am.

313
00:25:58.691 --> 00:25:59.850 line:82%
-Bahadur Singh?
-Yes.

314
00:25:59.934 --> 00:26:01.938 line:82%
-Are the gates clean?
-Yes.

315
00:26:02.411 --> 00:26:04.355 line:82%
Plant some new saplings.

316
00:26:04.438 --> 00:26:06.031 line:82%
You said the prayers without me?

317
00:26:06.823 --> 00:26:07.851 line:82%
Sanju!

318
00:26:12.907 --> 00:26:14.824 line:82%
Sorry, girlfriend, I'm late.

319
00:26:14.907 --> 00:26:18.064 line:82%
Not that late. There's still a lot to do.

320
00:26:19.178 --> 00:26:20.663 line:82%
That's what I'm here for.

321
00:26:20.746 --> 00:26:22.044 line:82%
-Hey, Sanju.
-Hello, Uncle!

322
00:26:22.128 --> 00:26:23.457 line:82%
There you are.

323
00:26:24.101 --> 00:26:25.626 line:82%
Very good. Very good.

324
00:26:25.710 --> 00:26:28.472 line:82%
-All set?
-All upset.

325
00:26:28.555 --> 00:26:31.007 line:82%
The engagement is next Sunday,
and everyone is in an uproar

326
00:26:31.590 --> 00:26:34.010 line:82%
I'm going into the office.
You take care of everything.

327
00:26:34.093 --> 00:26:35.330 line:82%
Is everyone here?

328
00:26:35.415 --> 00:26:37.852 line:82%
-Uncle, aunt...?
-Both

329
00:26:37.937 --> 00:26:42.533 line:82%
-I'm gonna make my entrance.
-You rascal, go in, I'll join you.

330
00:26:43.434 --> 00:26:45.896 line:82%
Uncle Shankar, bring in Sanjay's luggage.

331
00:26:45.980 --> 00:26:48.537 line:82%
-I'll be back in two hours.
-No, please...

332
00:26:48.610 --> 00:26:51.068 line:82%
Hey, girl, I'm gonna pull your hair.

333
00:26:51.152 --> 00:26:54.198 line:82%
-Hey, buddy
-Hey, buddy. Get back.

334
00:26:54.273 --> 00:26:57.041 line:82%
-Hi, Sanju, how are you?
-Good!

335
00:26:57.134 --> 00:27:01.120 line:82%
First, have you found someone
who can straighten you out?

336
00:27:01.203 --> 00:27:02.445 line:82%
A nice girl, like me?

337
00:27:02.538 --> 00:27:07.376 line:82%
What can I say? You married this
angry young man and broke my heart.

338
00:27:08.753 --> 00:27:12.923 line:82%
But I did find someone.
Now, I hear she's getting married too.

339
00:27:13.226 --> 00:27:15.384 line:82%
Oh, poor Sanju.

340
00:27:15.926 --> 00:27:19.740 line:82%
-Is she a nice girl?
-Nice? She's mind-blowing.

341
00:27:20.222 --> 00:27:24.393 line:82%
-What? More mind-blowing than me?
-How is that possible?

342
00:27:24.852 --> 00:27:27.139 line:82%
She's a little like you.

343
00:27:27.813 --> 00:27:30.027 line:82%
She could be your little sister.

344
00:27:32.500 --> 00:27:34.904 line:82%
But what does it matter now?

345
00:27:38.827 --> 00:27:40.623 line:82%
That boy is incorrigible.

346
00:27:40.701 --> 00:27:46.499 line:82%
-My obeisances to the aunt.
-Bless you.

347
00:27:46.582 --> 00:27:50.060 line:82%
Aren't you a little early
for a post-wedding appearance?

348
00:27:50.134 --> 00:27:53.798 line:82%
I would have come earlier,
but black cat crossed my path.

349
00:27:53.881 --> 00:27:57.359 line:82%
-Goodness! What happened?
-I took a detour to get here.

350
00:27:57.443 --> 00:28:01.840 line:82%
-It was the right thing to do.
-Forget that, tell me something.

351
00:28:01.904 --> 00:28:05.059 line:82%
-Have you seen Anju?
-I'll see her soon.

352
00:28:05.142 --> 00:28:08.604 line:82%
Meet her before I leave.
I mean, I have to go out.

353
00:28:08.687 --> 00:28:12.060 line:82%
-Hi, Sanjay.
-Hi, brother-in-law. How are you?

354
00:28:12.153 --> 00:28:13.222 line:82%
-How are you?
-Good.

355
00:28:13.305 --> 00:28:15.244 line:82%
How's Wall Street treating you?

356
00:28:15.328 --> 00:28:18.114 line:82%
-Cool. Anjali is upstairs.
-Upstairs. Anjali.

357
00:28:18.197 --> 00:28:20.086 line:82%
-Yes, go on.
-Go on.

358
00:28:20.169 --> 00:28:21.450 line:82%
Uncle Sanju.

359
00:28:21.909 --> 00:28:24.723 line:82%
Hi, Kutkut, you recognized me?

360
00:28:24.829 --> 00:28:29.491 line:82%
-Yes, and Grandpa wants to see you.
-Good Lord.

361
00:28:29.583 --> 00:28:32.663 line:82%
-Obeisances, uncle.
-Save the obeisances for later.

362
00:28:32.727 --> 00:28:35.881 line:82%
Did you get married secretly in Bombay?

363
00:28:35.965 --> 00:28:38.162 line:82%
-Good Lord.
-Good Lord.

364
00:28:38.265 --> 00:28:40.615 line:82%
I could never get married
without your approval.

365
00:28:41.709 --> 00:28:43.931 line:82%
Look at him, how understanding.

366
00:28:44.014 --> 00:28:49.812 line:82%
What a good boy. And then there's Anjali.
Have you seen Anjali yet?

367
00:28:50.762 --> 00:28:54.817 line:82%
-Sanju, you haven't seen Anjali yet?
-No, Nilu.

368
00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:57.755 line:82%
But why is everyone going on about Anjali?

369
00:28:58.102 --> 00:29:00.865 line:82%
-Sanju, what's this I hear?
-Hello, Grandma.

370
00:29:00.948 --> 00:29:03.889 line:82%
Bless you. You haven't seen Anju yet?

371
00:29:03.973 --> 00:29:06.120 line:82%
I will, please sit down.

372
00:29:06.203 --> 00:29:08.664 line:82%
-What's the hurry?
-But of course...

373
00:29:08.747 --> 00:29:11.459 line:82%
Sanju, there you are.
Anjali is waiting for you.

374
00:29:11.542 --> 00:29:13.921 line:82%
-Where?
-Upstairs. Come on.

375
00:29:14.006 --> 00:29:17.006 line:82%
-Let me say hi to everyone.
-Later. Now come along.

376
00:29:17.423 --> 00:29:20.153 line:82%
Come on, we've been waiting for you.

377
00:29:20.926 --> 00:29:23.839 line:82%
I mean, Anjali's been waiting.

378
00:29:23.929 --> 00:29:26.951 line:82%
-Waiting for me. Why?
-How should I know?

379
00:29:27.683 --> 00:29:29.902 line:82%
That's between you and Anjali.

380
00:29:29.977 --> 00:29:32.935 line:82%
Go on, she's waiting. Excuse me.

381
00:29:43.282 --> 00:29:45.075 line:82%
Now, he's ﬂoored.

382
00:29:46.202 --> 00:29:47.341 line:82%
Anjali.

383
00:29:56.694 --> 00:29:59.507 line:82%
Today, little Anju, you've had it.

384
00:29:59.590 --> 00:30:00.849 line:82%
You just wait.

385
00:30:04.476 --> 00:30:07.221 line:82%
Getting smart with Sanju?

386
00:30:07.304 --> 00:30:09.433 line:82%
Today, I'm gonna beat you!

387
00:30:09.517 --> 00:30:12.668 line:82%
You won't get away from me. Scared?

388
00:30:12.761 --> 00:30:14.957 line:82%
-You dog, you.
-What is it?

389
00:30:15.741 --> 00:30:17.107 line:82%
-Come. Come on.
-What?

390
00:30:17.191 --> 00:30:18.296 line:82%
What?

391
00:30:19.752 --> 00:30:21.529 line:82%
-Anju.
-Sanju.

392
00:30:23.434 --> 00:30:26.742 line:82%
-You won't get away from me now.
-Come on, come on.

393
00:30:29.168 --> 00:30:30.204 line:82%
Yes.

394
00:30:32.688 --> 00:30:33.715 line:82%
Got you.

395
00:30:50.182 --> 00:30:54.492 line:82%
-They're a nice couple, no?
-Yes.

396
00:30:56.040 --> 00:31:01.819 line:82%
Could've been better.
Could've been you.

397
00:31:04.655 --> 00:31:06.388 line:82%
That's what I always thought.

398
00:31:09.410 --> 00:31:14.873 line:82%
Whatever we may think,
marriages are made in heaven.

399
00:31:18.627 --> 00:31:20.236 line:82%
It could've been different.

400
00:31:21.380 --> 00:31:25.379 line:82%
Nilu could've been my Aunt Nilu.

401
00:31:28.387 --> 00:31:33.267 line:82%
If you're in love,
why is the heart afraid of love?

402
00:31:36.812 --> 00:31:38.822 line:82%
Greetings, sister-in-law.

403
00:31:38.896 --> 00:31:40.441 line:82%
-How are you?
-Hello, Mr. Khanna.

404
00:31:40.524 --> 00:31:42.610 line:82%
Weren't you supposed to come tomorrow?

405
00:31:42.693 --> 00:31:44.733 line:82%
I can leave if you want.

406
00:31:45.724 --> 00:31:48.157 line:82%
I just couldn't stay away.

407
00:31:48.824 --> 00:31:51.652 line:82%
I went to Delhi for few days,
but I couldn't stay there.

408
00:31:52.286 --> 00:31:56.607 line:82%
-Where's our girl? Where's Anjali?
-Anju!

409
00:31:56.692 --> 00:31:58.667 line:82%
-I'm here.
-There she is.

410
00:31:58.751 --> 00:32:02.331 line:82%
-Samosas. For you.
-Bless you.

411
00:32:03.816 --> 00:32:06.884 line:82%
No. First, what did you bring from Delhi?

412
00:32:06.967 --> 00:32:09.618 line:82%
Is she blackmailing me?

413
00:32:09.722 --> 00:32:12.306 line:82%
Wait till you're married.
Then I'll make you

414
00:32:12.389 --> 00:32:14.411 line:82%
cook hot samosas for me every day.

415
00:32:14.478 --> 00:32:18.020 line:82%
I could, but your son, the doctor,
will he let you eat fried food?

416
00:32:18.089 --> 00:32:19.178 line:82%
That's a good point.

417
00:32:19.249 --> 00:32:22.948 line:82%
Between you, me, and the samosas,
how did that fool crop up?

418
00:32:23.022 --> 00:32:24.234 line:82%
Uncle.

419
00:32:27.988 --> 00:32:29.171 line:82%
When will Rohit get here?

420
00:32:29.245 --> 00:32:31.950 line:82%
-Sanjay, come here.
-Yes.

421
00:32:32.636 --> 00:32:37.873 line:82%
-Sanjay is Mr. Malhotra's son.
-The late Mr. Malhotra?

422
00:32:38.374 --> 00:32:39.967 line:82%
-The one whose house I bought?
-Yes.

423
00:32:40.482 --> 00:32:44.226 line:82%
So, you're Sanjay.
I was hoping to meet you.

424
00:32:45.113 --> 00:32:47.247 line:82%
We've never met,
but I know your entire history.

425
00:32:47.851 --> 00:32:49.760 line:82%
Anju talks about you all the time.

426
00:32:49.843 --> 00:32:53.284 line:82%
When she's over she's always saying,
"This was Sanju's room,

427
00:32:53.357 --> 00:32:57.142 line:82%
this is where we played carom,"
so on and so forth.

428
00:32:58.435 --> 00:33:01.400 line:82%
Please come over someday.
It's your house.

429
00:33:01.927 --> 00:33:03.911 line:82%
It was. Now it's yours.

430
00:33:04.954 --> 00:33:08.487 line:82%
Anjali still calls it Sanju's house.

431
00:33:09.863 --> 00:33:12.551 line:82%
Silly, She doesn't even realize
where she's going.

432
00:33:13.450 --> 00:33:14.937 line:82%
Excuse me.

433
00:33:15.828 --> 00:33:18.599 line:82%
After Mr. Malhotra died in the accident,
he moved to Bombay.

434
00:33:19.397 --> 00:33:20.736 line:82%
He's doing well.

435
00:33:21.625 --> 00:33:25.066 line:82%
I wonder sometimes, destiny is strange.

436
00:33:25.838 --> 00:33:31.106 line:82%
He was motherless,
then, at 20, he lost his father too.

437
00:33:32.302 --> 00:33:33.562 line:82%
But he didn't break down.

438
00:33:35.863 --> 00:33:36.974 line:82%
He's a brave kid.

439
00:33:38.600 --> 00:33:40.078 line:82%
I like that boy.

440
00:33:40.561 --> 00:33:43.694 line:82%
-It's still here?
-Yes!

