00:50:26.733 --> 00:50:29.193 line:82%
Don't let this silly girl
pester you any longer.

664
00:50:30.501 --> 00:50:32.111 line:82%
She can ask me for anything she wants.

665
00:50:32.660 --> 00:50:35.611 line:82%
Rohit, what are you doing here?

666
00:50:35.700 --> 00:50:38.358 line:82%
Like you, I'm praying.

667
00:50:38.828 --> 00:50:40.022 line:82%
Rohit.

668
00:50:40.580 --> 00:50:43.179 line:82%
It doesn't feel right for you to be here.

669
00:50:44.121 --> 00:50:45.156 line:82%
Anjali.

670
00:50:46.711 --> 00:50:47.782 line:82%
Don't worry.

671
00:50:48.629 --> 00:50:50.458 line:82%
I asked your grandmother's permission.

672
00:50:51.048 --> 00:50:54.398 line:82%
-What have you done?
-I've fallen in love with you.

673
00:50:57.782 --> 00:51:01.267 line:82%
-Now what do you want?
-I've traveled a long way.

674
00:51:03.085 --> 00:51:04.353 line:82%
I should be rewarded.

675
00:51:05.234 --> 00:51:09.358 line:82%
A small hug. Half a kiss. Something.

676
00:51:10.526 --> 00:51:14.347 line:82%
Mr. Rohit Khanna. you're in a temple.

677
00:51:14.864 --> 00:51:18.624 line:82%
Oblations is all you'll get here.

678
00:51:23.122 --> 00:51:26.826 line:82%
I'm making do, Lord,
but you must intercede.

679
00:51:27.430 --> 00:51:28.544 line:82%
What rubbish.

680
00:51:28.628 --> 00:51:31.653 line:82%
How can he be better you?
Sanjay is the best.

681
00:51:32.253 --> 00:51:35.927 line:82%
No, Ria. I was overconfident.

682
00:51:36.981 --> 00:51:38.805 line:82%
But I don't compare to him.

683
00:51:38.888 --> 00:51:40.518 line:82%
Nothing. Zero.

684
00:51:41.858 --> 00:51:43.768 line:82%
That's what he said to me too.

685
00:51:47.438 --> 00:51:50.887 line:82%
I think I might make up an excuse
and leave tomorrow.

686
00:51:50.983 --> 00:51:52.081 line:82%
Sanju...

687
00:51:53.611 --> 00:51:54.882 line:82%
Sanju, listen to me.

688
00:51:55.786 --> 00:51:56.844 line:82%
Is Anjali there?

689
00:51:58.564 --> 00:51:59.645 line:82%
Where else would she be?

690
00:51:59.742 --> 00:52:03.751 line:82%
I mean, is she there with you?
Can you see her?

691
00:52:07.291 --> 00:52:09.332 line:82%
Yes, I can see her.

692
00:52:09.830 --> 00:52:11.087 line:82%
Only Anjali?

693
00:52:21.138 --> 00:52:27.139 line:82%
Do you see what you're leaving behind?
You did it once.

694
00:52:27.937 --> 00:52:30.834 line:82%
If you do it second time,
will you be able to forgive yourself?

695
00:52:32.108 --> 00:52:34.479 line:82%
Do you still want to come back?

696
00:52:35.987 --> 00:52:40.244 line:82%
No, not without Anjali.

697
00:52:40.917 --> 00:52:42.618 line:82%
And what about Rohit?

698
00:52:44.453 --> 00:52:49.542 line:82%
Rohit? Forget it, Ria.
Sanjay is the best.

699
00:52:54.462 --> 00:52:59.677 line:82%
There you are, Sanju. Anu and Rajesh
are expecting you for breakfast.

700
00:53:00.289 --> 00:53:03.764 line:82%
-They're serving stuffed fried pancakes.
-I prefer this.

701
00:53:03.848 --> 00:53:07.481 line:82%
Put that back.
It's an offering to the gods.

702
00:53:07.565 --> 00:53:08.895 line:82%
Girlfriend.

703
00:53:10.883 --> 00:53:11.898 line:82%
Okay.

704
00:53:14.053 --> 00:53:17.194 line:82%
Go see Anjali. She hasn't had breakfast.

705
00:53:17.278 --> 00:53:19.951 line:82%
She isn't out of bed. What's she up to?

706
00:53:21.908 --> 00:53:24.076 line:82%
-Say it again.
-Anjali.

707
00:53:26.554 --> 00:53:30.917 line:82%
My name sounds so different
when you say it.

708
00:53:32.418 --> 00:53:33.589 line:82%
Say my full name.

709
00:53:34.170 --> 00:53:35.326 line:82%
Anjali Sharma.

710
00:53:35.421 --> 00:53:37.748 line:82%
No stupid, not this one.

711
00:53:38.966 --> 00:53:40.358 line:82%
The name I'm going to have.

712
00:53:43.678 --> 00:53:48.100 line:82%
Anjali Khanna. Mrs. Anjali R. Khanna.

713
00:53:48.201 --> 00:53:51.103 line:82%
Anju, your mother wants you downstairs.

714
00:53:51.187 --> 00:53:54.131 line:82%
Rohit, I'll have to hang up now,
okay? Bye.

715
00:53:54.840 --> 00:53:55.871 line:82%
Okay.

716
00:53:56.502 --> 00:53:57.652 line:82%
Hang up.

717
00:53:59.169 --> 00:54:00.556 line:82%
No, you hang up.

718
00:54:00.655 --> 00:54:04.779 line:82%
I can't hang up until you hang up.

719
00:54:05.593 --> 00:54:06.827 line:82%
Hang up.

720
00:54:08.579 --> 00:54:10.888 line:82%
No, you.

721
00:54:12.747 --> 00:54:14.001 line:82%
I told you.

722
00:54:14.877 --> 00:54:18.219 line:82%
Let's do it on the count of three.

723
00:54:19.715 --> 00:54:20.933 line:82%
One.

724
00:54:21.717 --> 00:54:22.899 line:82%
Two.

725
00:54:23.636 --> 00:54:24.709 line:82%
Three.

726
00:54:25.137 --> 00:54:26.681 line:82%
You also didn't hang up.

727
00:54:28.432 --> 00:54:31.102 line:82%
-Oh, Rohit, you're crazy.
-Crazy.

728
00:54:34.146 --> 00:54:35.773 line:82%
How many times?

729
00:54:36.649 --> 00:54:37.845 line:82%
I love you.

730
00:54:39.443 --> 00:54:40.675 line:82%
Hang up. Please.

731
00:54:41.917 --> 00:54:44.907 line:82%
Hang up.

732
00:54:44.991 --> 00:54:46.617 line:82%
Done. Now, come on.

733
00:54:49.810 --> 00:54:50.878 line:82%
Hung up?

734
00:54:50.970 --> 00:54:53.874 line:82%
I scream, you scream.
Hey, girls. How are you doing?

735
00:54:53.958 --> 00:54:55.760 line:82%
-Cool, man.
-Exactly the same.

736
00:54:55.833 --> 00:54:59.005 line:82%
Okay, this is mine.

737
00:54:59.547 --> 00:55:01.751 line:82%
-Rohit, your chocolate.
-Thanks.

738
00:55:01.842 --> 00:55:04.135 line:82%
And, ma'am, your boring strawberry.

739
00:55:04.802 --> 00:55:06.164 line:82%
Why is it boring?

740
00:55:07.077 --> 00:55:10.683 line:82%
You'll only find out
if you ever try another flavor.

741
00:55:10.756 --> 00:55:13.102 line:82%
Have you ever tried anything
other than strawberry?

742
00:55:14.770 --> 00:55:18.406 line:82%
It's not your fault, though.
It's your life that's boring.

743
00:55:19.025 --> 00:55:22.967 line:82%
Look at me, some black currant,
some mango, dash of mint.

744
00:55:23.070 --> 00:55:26.901 line:82%
Lollipop, also.
Variety, my dear, is the spice of life.

745
00:55:27.867 --> 00:55:30.119 line:82%
Right? What do you say, Rohit?

746
00:55:31.954 --> 00:55:35.558 line:82%
But, actually, when I look at you,
I think your life's boring too.

747
00:55:36.459 --> 00:55:41.141 line:82%
Don't mind, but I'm sure Anjali
is the first and only girl in your life.

748
00:55:41.235 --> 00:55:42.304 line:82%
Of course not.

749
00:55:45.051 --> 00:55:50.147 line:82%
You mean you've had girlfriends?
Before Anjali?

750
00:55:50.241 --> 00:55:52.600 line:82%
-Excuse me, sir.
-Yes.

751
00:55:55.019 --> 00:55:56.036 line:82%
Wow.

752
00:55:56.479 --> 00:55:59.717 line:82%
Great, dude. Looks can be quite deceptive.

753
00:55:59.815 --> 00:56:01.649 line:82%
Rohit? Girlfriend?

754
00:56:03.360 --> 00:56:05.472 line:82%
What do you mean, girlfriends?

755
00:56:06.906 --> 00:56:09.988 line:82%
Girlfriends are girls who are friends.

756
00:56:10.951 --> 00:56:14.710 line:82%
But more girl than friend, right?

757
00:56:18.167 --> 00:56:21.432 line:82%
Rohit, how come I've never heard
about your girlfriends?

758
00:56:22.071 --> 00:56:26.217 line:82%
Maybe because... You don't know?

759
00:56:26.922 --> 00:56:29.720 line:82%
You never told her? Very bad.

760
00:56:29.804 --> 00:56:34.074 line:82%
I wanted to tell you, but you aid
you weren't interested in my past.

761
00:56:34.160 --> 00:56:38.575 line:82%
Okay. Fine. I wasn't. Now I am.

762
00:56:38.671 --> 00:56:40.773 line:82%
Yes, me too. Go on, tell us.

763
00:56:41.524 --> 00:56:45.820 line:82%
Fine, anyway our relationship
is based on truth.

764
00:56:46.612 --> 00:56:49.098 line:82%
Ask whatever you want.
You have the right to know.

765
00:56:50.157 --> 00:56:53.661 line:82%
-Well--
-Well, for starters, Mr. Rohit Khanna,

766
00:56:53.744 --> 00:56:57.857 line:82%
what I, we want to know is,
how many girlfriends?

767
00:56:57.948 --> 00:56:59.050 line:82%
Yeah.

768
00:56:59.959 --> 00:57:02.253 line:82%
-Let me think.
-Yes, go on.

769
00:57:02.336 --> 00:57:05.826 line:82%
I think, four. No, actually, five.

770
00:57:06.590 --> 00:57:11.896 line:82%
Five? How long ago was the fifth?

771
00:57:13.139 --> 00:57:15.501 line:82%
About three months.

772
00:57:16.128 --> 00:57:19.854 line:82%
When you were seeing me,
you already had a girlfriend?

773
00:57:20.855 --> 00:57:22.119 line:82%
Yes, but...

774
00:57:23.584 --> 00:57:27.361 line:82%
when I saw you for the first time
I realized that you were the girl

775
00:57:27.444 --> 00:57:29.462 line:82%
I wanted to spend my life with.

776
00:57:31.282 --> 00:57:33.808 line:82%
I told her, and she understood.

777
00:57:34.368 --> 00:57:37.188 line:82%
Really? That's so amazing.

778
00:57:37.606 --> 00:57:40.833 line:82%
Come on, Anjali.
Why get worked up over that?

779
00:57:40.916 --> 00:57:46.981 line:82%
Everyone has a past. It's natural.
If you had a past, I wouldn't get upset.

780
00:57:48.042 --> 00:57:50.759 line:82%
Anjali's past. I'm Anjali's past.

781
00:57:51.690 --> 00:57:54.430 line:82%
In her boring life,
there was no friend, except me.

782
00:57:54.513 --> 00:57:56.557 line:82%
So there's no chance
of your getting upset.

783
00:57:56.640 --> 00:58:01.530 line:82%
Sanjay, stay out of it.
Listen, Rohit, I'm really hurt, okay.

784
00:58:02.166 --> 00:58:04.190 line:82%
You shouldn't have hidden it from me.

785
00:58:04.273 --> 00:58:05.503 line:82%
What's there to hide?

786
00:58:06.011 --> 00:58:07.568 line:82%
Why didn't you tell me?

787
00:58:08.569 --> 00:58:11.223 line:82%
What's there to tell, Anjali?

788
00:58:11.322 --> 00:58:14.935 line:82%
Nothing to be said and nothing to hide?
What's this all about?

789
00:58:15.019 --> 00:58:17.912 line:82%
-Nothing. It's nothing, Anjali--
-Nothing?

790
00:58:18.696 --> 00:58:24.043 line:82%
My fiancé has had five affairs
and I didn't know about it until now?

791
00:58:24.126 --> 00:58:26.849 line:82%
Three happened when I was in school.
We were kids.

792
00:58:26.939 --> 00:58:28.254 line:82%
I don't want to hear anything.

793
00:58:30.299 --> 00:58:32.493 line:82%
Come on, Anjali, people are staring.

794
00:58:32.579 --> 00:58:34.136 line:82%
Okay. Fine.

795
00:58:34.637 --> 00:58:38.224 line:82%
I don't want to embarrass you
even one more minute, Mr. Rohit Khanna.

796
00:58:39.228 --> 00:58:41.685 line:82%
-I'm going.
-You can't be serious.

797
00:58:41.769 --> 00:58:43.299 line:82%
-Sanju.
-Anju.

798
00:58:43.938 --> 00:58:46.607 line:82%
Sanju, will you drive me home
or shall I go on my own?

799
00:58:46.690 --> 00:58:50.903 line:82%
Can't I finish my ice cream?
No. Okay.

800
00:58:50.986 --> 00:58:53.670 line:82%
Anjali, Anjali.

801
00:58:53.764 --> 00:58:56.922 line:82%
No hard feelings, buddy. Got to go. Sorry.

802
00:58:58.532 --> 00:59:01.080 line:82%
No, I'm sorry.

803
00:59:02.957 --> 00:59:04.500 line:82%
My fault.

804
00:59:06.393 --> 00:59:08.671 line:82%
No, Rohit, it's not your fault,

805
00:59:09.810 --> 00:59:11.079 line:82%
but I have to do it.

806
00:59:12.591 --> 00:59:19.075 line:82%
You're so nice,
but that's also why you have to die.

807
00:59:22.601 --> 00:59:27.769 line:82%
You gotta go, Rohit. Away from Anjali.
Far away. Forever.

808
00:59:29.735 --> 00:59:30.813 line:82%
Goodbye.

809
00:59:44.373 --> 00:59:45.642 line:82%
Poor guy.

810
00:59:47.543 --> 00:59:48.794 line:82%
He was a nice guy.

811
00:59:54.174 --> 00:59:56.844 line:82%
Hey, you. Take it easy, man.

812
00:59:57.594 --> 00:59:59.193 line:82%
Come on. Get up.

813
01:00:00.222 --> 01:00:01.460 line:82%
Thanks, buddy.

814
01:00:01.822 --> 01:00:03.770 line:82%
-I should be thanking you.
-Really?

815
01:00:04.584 --> 01:00:08.299 line:82%
You played a major role in cementing
my relationship with Anjali.

816
01:00:09.023 --> 01:00:10.065 line:82%
How come?

817
01:00:11.025 --> 01:00:16.397 line:82%
In America, Anjali told me
about the swing you rigged up for her.

818
01:00:17.239 --> 01:00:19.263 line:82%
It's a cherished childhood memory for her.

819
01:00:20.367 --> 01:00:23.204 line:82%
-So, guess what I did.
-What?

820
01:00:23.273 --> 01:00:27.541 line:82%
I rigged up a swing too
and I decorated it with flowers.

821
01:00:28.959 --> 01:00:32.744 line:82%
I kept her eyes shut as I took her to
the swing, and that's when I asked her,

822
01:00:33.839 --> 01:00:36.900 line:82%
"Anjali, will you marry me?"

823
01:00:38.807 --> 01:00:42.564 line:82%
She opened her eyes, saw the swing,

824
01:00:44.308 --> 01:00:45.917 line:82%
and she gave me a small smile.

825
01:00:49.104 --> 01:00:54.109 line:82%
I'm still not sure
if she was smiling at me or the swing.

826
01:00:55.527 --> 01:00:57.004 line:82%
The swing, of course.

827
01:00:59.073 --> 01:01:00.282 line:82%
Sanju, you also...

828
01:01:00.366 --> 01:01:03.077 line:82%
Yesterday, Anjali behaved badly with you.

829
01:01:03.160 --> 01:01:05.474 line:82%
If I were you, I'd stop talking to her.

830
01:01:06.123 --> 01:01:10.709 line:82%
-What? I was about to call her.
-Don't be silly.

831
01:01:10.793 --> 01:01:14.046 line:82%
Have you seen Rajesh?
You'll end up like him. Hen-pecked.

832
01:01:14.129 --> 01:01:16.840 line:82%
-Take my advice, you needn't call her.
-Why?

833
01:01:16.924 --> 01:01:20.135 line:82%
What do you mean why? She fought with you.
Let her call and apologize.

834
01:01:20.719 --> 01:01:24.604 line:82%
-But, Sanjay...
-Trust me, I know her.

835
01:01:24.678 --> 01:01:26.014 line:82%
Don't say anything.

836
01:01:26.100 --> 01:01:29.036 line:82%
Tonight, at the engagement,
she'll apologize.

837
01:01:29.129 --> 01:01:30.604 line:82%
-It's not your fault
-I know.

838
01:01:31.188 --> 01:01:32.905 line:82%
-Here.
-Yes, I'm doing that.

839
01:01:36.735 --> 01:01:38.765 line:82%
How about a light massage?

840
01:01:38.859 --> 01:01:40.187 line:82%
-Look at him.
-It's the way he is.

841
01:01:40.714 --> 01:01:43.033 line:82%
What did Rohit say today on the phone?

842
01:01:44.493 --> 01:01:46.278 line:82%
Nothing.

843
01:01:46.362 --> 01:01:49.275 line:82%
-Surely he said something.
-He hasn't called until now.

844
01:01:50.380 --> 01:01:54.545 line:82%
-Doesn't he call every morning?
-Except for this morning.

845
01:01:54.628 --> 01:01:58.118 line:82%
-Maybe he's out jogging...
-No. He returned an hour ago.

846
01:01:58.939 --> 01:02:02.369 line:82%
-Was he all right?
-He was just fine.

847
01:02:02.911 --> 01:02:07.599 line:82%
Said he'd had a good night's sleep.
He was looking very fresh.

848
01:02:08.016 --> 01:02:11.770 line:82%
-I think he's still annoyed at me.
-Yes, he is.

849
01:02:12.271 --> 01:02:16.525 line:82%
-That's why he never called.
-Just like a typical man.

850
01:02:17.359 --> 01:02:22.656 line:82%
He's not crazy, like me. In his place,
I would've called ten times already.

851
01:02:23.288 --> 01:02:26.160 line:82%
I would've realized my mistake
and I would've apologized.

852
01:02:26.243 --> 01:02:29.134 line:82%
But not Rohit, he'll never do that.

853
01:02:29.760 --> 01:02:31.081 line:82%
Because he knows

854
01:02:31.165 --> 01:02:35.105 line:82%
if he takes the first step,
you will always have the upper hand.

855
01:02:35.544 --> 01:02:37.838 line:82%
And he's not one to be hen-pecked.

856
01:02:39.298 --> 01:02:40.717 line:82%
He's so smart.

857
01:02:41.550 --> 01:02:45.471 line:82%
I could never be as clever.
When I get married,

858
01:02:46.013 --> 01:02:48.392 line:82%
I'll be totally hen-pecked.

859
01:02:49.057 --> 01:02:50.083 line:82%
Always.

860
01:02:52.436 --> 01:02:53.937 line:82%
That's for me? Thank you.

861
01:02:55.772 --> 01:02:58.817 line:82%
You wanted to call him, didn't you?

862
01:02:59.518 --> 01:03:03.447 line:82%
Go ahead and apologize.
He isn't made of stone. He'll forgive you.

863
01:03:04.998 --> 01:03:06.575 line:82%
Why should Anjali apologize?

864
01:03:06.658 --> 01:03:09.912 line:82%
Rohit is at fault. He's the one who made
a mountain out of a molehill yesterday.

865
01:03:09.995 --> 01:03:14.920 line:82%
Anu, he's Anjali's fiancé.
She can misbehave with her friends.

866
01:03:15.013 --> 01:03:18.962 line:82%
-She can do it with, me, but Rohit--
-I can do it to Rohit too.

867
01:03:19.700 --> 01:03:22.633 line:82%
And you shouldn't take Rohit's side.

868
01:03:23.417 --> 01:03:25.219 line:82%
Whose friend are you? Mine or his?

869
01:03:26.580 --> 01:03:28.256 line:82%
And for your kind information,

870
01:03:28.352 --> 01:03:32.434 line:82%
I won't to talk to him unless he calls me.

871
01:03:33.066 --> 01:03:34.728 line:82%
Tell your clever friend that.

872
01:03:34.811 --> 01:03:36.088 line:82%
But, Anjali...

873
01:03:38.482 --> 01:03:39.718 line:82%
Anu...

874
01:03:41.860 --> 01:03:44.444 line:82%
Sanjay, you're a genius.

875
01:04:00.170 --> 01:04:01.460 line:82%
Nice couple.

876
01:04:04.049 --> 01:04:05.287 line:82%
Could be nicer.

877
01:04:06.802 --> 01:04:11.431 line:82%
Could be someone else.
Could be... you?

878
01:04:14.893 --> 01:04:19.147 line:82%
Didn't I tell you,
marriages are made in heaven.

879
01:04:21.400 --> 01:04:26.837 line:82%
And I say, follow your heart
and you can change the world.

880
01:04:29.241 --> 01:04:30.258 line:82%
Meaning?

881
01:04:31.591 --> 01:04:34.037 line:82%
It's just an engagement.

